Near the corner of the large basin is a lake, completely frozen over by the cold of the area. The ice is fairly solid, enough to take a decent amount of weight (i.e someone of average weight jumping on it), but enough force would definitely cause it to cave in. You could use the ice skating boots from the #main-lobby , and it would be mostly safe. Probably. A sort of "arena" forms around the lake, with trees marking the outskirts of it. If you were to skirt off the lake, you could probably crash into one of these trees. Interestingly, some odd little animals seems to be gliding around the frozen lake, playing around. This seems to be their natural habitat. Further research indicates that these are "snow monkeys" or Japanese macaques. Some of them seem to have buried themselves in the snow banks nearby, sleeping.
